Ferdinand Schumann-Heink https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ferdinand_Schumann-Heink 0 Ernestine Schumann-Heink (15 June 1861 – 17 November 1936) was a Czech-born German-American operatic contralto of German Bohemian descent. She was noted for the size, beauty, tonal richness, flexibility and wide range of her voice.
